aa(lp25
VAttached to the facial bones
p26
aVthat define our face's structure
p27
aVare the muscles that deliver our facial expression,
p28
aVour universal language of expression,
p29
aVour social-signaling system.
p30
aVAnd overlying this is the skin drape,
p31
aVwhich is a hugely complex
p32
aVthree-dimensional structure \u2014
p33
aVtaking right-angled bends here and there,
p34
aVhaving thin areas like the eyelids,
p35
aVthick areas like the cheek, different colors.
p36
aVAnd then we have the sensual factor of the face.
p37
aVWhere do we like to kiss people?
p38
aVOn the lips. Nibble the ears maybe.
p39
aVIt's the face where we're attracted to with that.
