aa(lp49
VDysmorphophobia
p50
aVis an extreme version
p51
aVof the fact that we don't see ourselves
p52
aVas others see us.
p53
aVIt's a shocking truth
p54
aVthat we only see mirror images of ourselves,
p55
aVand we only see ourselves
p56
aVin freeze-frame photographic images
p57
aVthat capture a mere fraction of the time that we live.
p58
aVDysmorphophobia
p59
aVis a perversion of this
p60
aVwhere people who may be very good looking
p61
aVregard themselves as hideously ugly
p62
aVand are constantly seeking surgery
p63
aVto correct their facial appearance.
p64
aVThey don't need this. They need psychiatric help.
p65
aVMax has kindly donated his photograph to me.
p66
aVHe doesn't have dysmorphophobia, but I'm using his photograph
p67
aVto illustrate the fact that he looks exactly like a dysmorphophobic.
p68
aVIn other words, he looks entirely normal.
