aa(lp102
VAs teenagers \u2014
p103
aVjust think back to your teenage years \u2014
p104
aVwe're going through a dramatic
p105
aVand often disproportionate change
p106
aVin our facial appearance.
p107
aVWe're trying to struggle to find our identity.
p108
aVWe crave the approval of our peers.
p109
aVSo our facial appearance is vital to us
p110
aVas we're trying to project ourselves to the world.
p111
aVJust remember that single acne spot
p112
aVthat crippled you for several days.
p113
aVHow long did you spend looking in the mirror every day,
p114
aVpracticing your sardonic look, practicing your serious look,
p115
aVtrying to look like Sean Connery, as I did,
p116
aVtrying to raise one eyebrow?
p117
aVIt's a crippling time.
