aa(lp119
VI've chosen to show this profile view of Sue
p120
aVbecause what it shows is her lower jaw jutting forward
p121
aVand her lower lip jutting forward.
p122
aVI'd like you all in the audience now to push your lower jaw forward.
p123
aVTurn to the person next to you,
p124
aVpush your lower jaws forward. Turn to the person next to you
p125
aVand look at them \u2014 they look miserable.
p126
aVThat's exactly what people used to say to Sue.
p127
aVShe wasn't miserable at all.
p128
aVBut people used to say to her, "Why are you so miserable?"
p129
aVPeople were making misjudgments all the time
p130
aVon her mood.
p131
aVTeachers and peers were underestimating her; she was teased at school.
p132
aVSo she chose to have facial surgery.
p133
aVAfter the facial surgery,
p134
aVshe said, "My face now reflects my personality.
p135
aVPeople know now that I'm enthusiastic,
p136
aVthat I'm a happy person."
p137
aVAnd that's the change that can be achieved for teenagers.
