aa(lp190
VHenriapi illustrates this phenomenon as well.
p191
aVThis is a man in his 20s
p192
aVwhose first visit out of Nigeria was with this malignant cancer
p193
aVthat he came to the United Kingdom to have operated on.
p194
aVIt was my longest operation.
p195
aVIt took 23 hours. I did it with my neurosurgeon.
p196
aVWe removed all the bones at the right side of his face \u2014
p197
aVhis eye, his nose,
p198
aVthe skull bones, the facial skin \u2014
p199
aVand reconstructed him with tissue from the back.
p200
aVHe continued to work as a psychiatric nurse.
p201
aVHe got married. He had a son called Jeremiah.
p202
aVAnd again, he said,
p203
aV"This painting of me with my son Jeremiah
p204
aVshows me as the successful man that I feel that I am."
p205
aVHis facial disfigurement
p206
aVdid not affect him
p207
aVbecause he had the support of a family;
p208
aVhe had a successful, fulfilling job.
